  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<em>This feat allows you to acquire a powerful familiar, but only when you could normally acquire a new familiar.</em><br/><br/><b>Prerequisites</b><br/>Ability to acquire a new familiar, compatible alignment, sufficiently high level (see below).<br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>When choosing a familiar, the creatures listed below are also available to you. You may choose a familiar with an alignment up to one step away on each alignment axis (lawful through chaotic, good through evil).<br/><br/>You can find the full list of available Improved Familiars here.<br/><br/>Improved familiars otherwise use the rules for regular familiars, with two exceptions: if the creature's type is something other than animal, its type does not change; and improved familiars do not gain the ability to speak with other creatures of their kind (although many of them already have the ability to communicate).",
